snippet.textDisplay: Javed Bashir, undoubtedly a classical music supremo. The way he took those variations, I was breathless just listening to it, imagine how difficult it would be to sing it. But he does it so effortlessly showing the years of riyaaz and prayers that has made him such a genius. He connects us to the Almighty through his music, his songs in Bhaag Milkha Bhaag were so magical. Keep belting out such soulful nos and making us inch closer to HIM.
snippet.textOriginal: Javed Bashir, undoubtedly a classical music supremo. The way he took those variations, I was breathless just listening to it, imagine how difficult it would be to sing it. But he does it so effortlessly showing the years of riyaaz and prayers that has made him such a genius. snippet.textDisplay: Ofcourse there's no denying what Javed Bashir has done in this performance. But I'd like to highlight what Ali Azmat has achieved. I mean, everytime I hear the part from 3:25, I end up crying. Like Everytime. Truly kaisa zamana hoga voh. Gosh. It's so right to the point. And the way Azmat delivers it really makes you believe the importance of that part. That is true Soulful and Soul filling delivery.
